1. Purpose

GeoAtlas is a geospatial reasoning system that helps operators, founders, and investors decide where a business should go and why.

It combines:
	•	map geometry
	•	buildings and places
	•	mobility and accessibility
	•	neighborhood economics
	•	competitive landscape
	•	semantic signals from text
	•	business outcome prediction

Core output:
	•	ranked candidate sites
	•	expected performance band
	•	risk flags
	•	analog locations
	•	human-readable reasoning

