3. Core services

A. Ingestion service

Pulls and normalizes raw world data.

Responsibilities:
	•	fetch raw datasets
	•	validate schemas
	•	standardize geometry
	•	assign IDs
	•	write staged data

Inputs:
	•	places
	•	buildings
	•	road networks
	•	transit
	•	demographics
	•	listings
	•	reviews
	•	permits

Outputs:
	•	normalized parquet
	•	PostGIS tables
	•	lineage metadata

⸻

B. Entity resolution service

Turns messy sources into canonical objects.

Responsibilities:
	•	dedupe duplicate places
	•	merge address variants
	•	map source records to one place_id or site_id
	•	score confidence of merges

Key problem:
This becomes one of the real moats.

⸻

C. World model service

Builds the city as a queryable graph.

Responsibilities:
	•	H3 tiling
	•	building/place joins
	•	neighborhood aggregation
	•	trade area generation
	•	graph edge construction

Objects:
	•	Cell
	•	Place
	•	Site
	•	TradeArea
	•	MarketGraph

⸻

D. Feature service

Builds model features by site and by cell.

Feature families:
	•	geometry
	•	access
	•	competition
	•	economics
	•	temporal
	•	semantics
	•	graph spillovers

Outputs:
	•	feature tables
	•	feature snapshots by date
	•	model-ready matrices

⸻

E. Model service

Trains and serves predictive models.

Models:
	•	site retrieval / analog matching
	•	opportunity ranking
	•	revenue band prediction
	•	survival probability
	•	cannibalization risk
	•	uncertainty / calibration

Outputs:
	•	scored sites
	•	prediction intervals
	•	feature attributions

⸻

F. Simulation service

Runs what-if scenarios.

Examples:
	•	“What if rent is 15% higher?”
	•	“What if a competitor opens within 500m?”
	•	“What if transit access improves?”
	•	“What if we add two more sites?”

⸻

G. LLM explainer service

Converts structured model outputs into usable language.

Rules:
	•	it never invents the underlying score
	•	it only explains what the structured layer produced
	•	it cites top features and analogs
	•	it flags uncertainty clearly

⸻

H. API service

Exposes the product.

Endpoints:
	•	search candidate markets
	•	score a site
	•	simulate a location
	•	find analog neighborhoods
	•	explain a ranking
	•	upload operator portfolio

