7. Model stack

Retrieval model

Goal:
Find analog locations and analog businesses.

Methods:
	•	embedding similarity
	•	nearest neighbors on feature vectors
	•	hybrid retrieval: semantic + tabular

Output:
“show me places like our best store”

⸻

Ranking model

Goal:
Produce site ordering.

Inputs:
all engineered features

Outputs:
	•	opportunity score
	•	ranked candidates

Good starter:
	•	LightGBM / XGBoost ranker

⸻

Revenue band model

Goal:
Predict likely gross revenue band.

Outputs:
	•	low
	•	mid
	•	high

Use:
	•	quantile regression or separate quantile models

⸻

Survival model

Goal:
Probability a location survives X months.

Use:
	•	12-month
	•	24-month
	•	36-month survival

⸻

Cannibalization model

Goal:
Estimate how much a new site steals from existing same-brand sites.

Needed for:
	•	chains
	•	portfolio expansion

⸻

Uncertainty model

Goal:
Tell user how much to trust a score.

Drivers:
	•	sparse data
	•	low analog quality
	•	unstable neighborhood
	•	model disagreement

⸻

8. Scoring design

Opportunity score

Composite but transparent.

Opportunity =
  DemandFit
+ AccessFit
+ Complementarity
+ GrowthMomentum
- CompetitionPressure
- OccupancyCostPressure
- OperationalFriction

Each component normalized to 0–100.

Confidence score

Confidence =
  DataCoverage
+ AnalogQuality
+ SignalAgreement
- Volatility
- Missingness

Never hide uncertainty.

